description: SpaceX successfully launched 24 Starlink satellites aboard its Falcon 9 rocket from Cape Canaveral Space Force Station on November 30 at 12:00 a.m. EST. The mission aimed to enhance the company’s global internet network by adding to its expanding satellite megaconstellation in low-Earth orbit. The Falcon 9's first stage booster, identified as B1083, returned safely to Earth, landing on the droneship.
title: SpaceX Falcon 9 Launches 24 Starlink Satellites to Expand Internet Network

description: NASA’s satellite images have captured the ongoing volcanic eruption near Iceland's Blue Lagoon. The eruption, which started on 20 November, caused lava to flow from a fissure, with the nearby Blue Lagoon spa and Grindavík being evacuated. The infrared visuals reveal lava glowing brighter than Reykjavík. While the eruption is ongoing, lava flow has slowed since the initial event.
title: NASA Captures Stream of Lava Flowing from Iceland’s Volcanic Eruption

description: Group Captain Shubhanshu Shukla and backup astronaut Group Captain Prasanth Balakrishnan Nair, selected for India's historic Gaganyaan mission, have completed the first phase of their training in collaboration with NASA. The training, which began in August 2024, was designed to prepare the astronauts for their roles in India’s first-ever human spaceflight, scheduled for late 2026.
title: Gaganyaan Astronauts Finish First Phase of Training for ISRO-NASA Joint Mission

description: The Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) has announced plans for the Bharatiya Antariksha Station (BAS), a space station designed to advance India’s space exploration efforts. Initially, the BAS will support a crew of three astronauts, with plans to expand this capacity to six in the future. The station will serve as a platform for a variety of scientific research, including interplanetary studies, life sciences, and medicine, with a particular focus on understanding the effects of microgravity on human health.
title: ISRO Reveals How Many Astronauts Will Be Hosted on the Bharatiya Antariksh Station: Report

description: An international team of archaeologists is investigating a shipwreck discovered off the coast of Malindi, Kenya, which may be the remains of the São Jorge, a Portuguese galleon linked to Vasco da Gama's final voyage. The wreck, found in 2013, lies on a coral reef approximately 500 meters from the shore and is believed to have sunk over 500 years ago. Artifacts retrieved from the site, including elephant tusks and copper ingots, suggest the ship’s Portuguese origins. The team, composed of researchers from the University of Coimbra, the National Museum of Kenya, and the Bergen Maritime Museum, has been carefully studying the wreck and its surrounding area to confirm its identity. If the São Jorge is confirmed, it would provide significant insight into early 16th-century maritime history.
title: Shipwreck Off Kenya's Coast Could Be Galleon Linked to Vasco da Gama's Final Voyage

description: A new study published in the American Journal of Primatology uses advanced 3D scanning technology to examine fossilized bones and muscle insertion points, shedding light on the evolution of bipedalism in human ancestors. Led by Professor Josep M. Potau from the University of Barcelona, the research suggests that early hominins, like Australopithecus and Paranthropus, combined bipedal locomotion with tree-climbing, similar to modern bonobos.
title: Advanced 3D Fossil Scans Provide Clues to the Origins of Bipedalism in Human Evolution

description: NASA’s Curiosity rover is set to explore Martian "spiderweb" formations, known as boxwork, which may reveal secrets about the planet’s ancient watery past. These unique structures, first observed decades ago, could help scientists understand Mars' history of water and the potential for past life. The rover’s investigation aims to study minerals left by ancient lakes and oceans, providing further insight into the planet's potential for supporting life.
title: NASA’s Curiosity Rover Set to Target Spiderweb-Like 'Boxworks Deposits' on Mars' Surface

description: WhatsApp is beta testing a feature that lets users share, view, and follow WhatsApp Channels using a quick response code (QR code) code in the app. The feature is currently available to beta testers and could roll out to all WhatsApp users in the future.
title: WhatsApp Starts Testing Feature to View, Share Channels Using QR Codes

description: After a communication failure caused by a power glitch in October, NASA has restored contact with Voyager 1. The spacecraft, now 15.4 billion miles away, continues to transmit data from its remaining instruments. The probe's systems were affected by energy limitations, but the problem was resolved in November, allowing its scientific mission to continue.
title: NASA Restores Communications with Voyager 1, Ending 2023 Power Glitch

description: Researchers from the University of Arizona have uncovered evidence of a powerful solar storm that occurred between 664 and 663 BCE, known as a Miyake Event. The discovery was made by analysing radiocarbon spikes in ancient tree rings, which act as natural records of past solar activity. These rare events, first identified in 2012, occur when solar radiation dramatically increases, leaving a trace in both tree rings and ice cores.
title: Evidence of Massive Solar Storm Strike on Earth 2,700 Years Ago Found in Tree Rings

description: The James Webb Space Telescope has captured groundbreaking images of Westerlund 1, a supermassive star cluster located 12,000 light-years away. The new findings offer a closer look at star formation processes, particularly the discovery of brown dwarfs, and highlight the role of energetic radiation in shaping planetary environments.
title: James Webb Space Telescope Reveals Surprising Details of Westerlund 1 Star Cluster

description: Oppo is said to be working on three smartphone models that could be equipped with batteries that have a capacity of more than 6,000mAh. A tipster claims that the Chinese phone maker is already developing two smartphones that could pack up to 7,000mAh batteries. Realme has also been tipped to launch a smartphone with a 7,00mAh battery in December.
title: Oppo Working on Three Smartphones With Up to 7,000mAh Batteries, Tipster Claims

description: Ethereum is confronting critical questions about its role in supporting crypto commerce, following changes to the user experience that are said to have diminished activity. According to critics, there has been a rising dependence on Layer-2 blockchains, which are developed to enhance time consuming and expensive transactions.
title: Crypto’s ‘Middle Child’ Ethereum Flounders as Rivals Gain Ground

description: OnePlus 13R has been listed on Geekbench, and the purported successor to the OnePlus 12R could soon be launched. The handset is expected to debut in global markets in the coming months, alongside the flagship OnePlus 13 model. Here's what we know about the upcoming OnePlus 13R and is specifications.
title: OnePlus 13R Specifications Revealed via Geekbench Listing, Could Launch Soon

description: OpenAI has been sued by five news publications in Canada: Torstar, Postmedia, The Globe and Mail, The Canadian Press, and CBC/Radio-Canada over alleged copyright infringement. The five news companies have accused the ChatGPT maker of regularly breaching copyright and online terms of use.
title: OpenAI Sued by Canadian News Companies Over Alleged Copyright Breaches
